name: Underpasses Are Liminal Places
description: We approach underpasses with trepidation, whether instinctively, or not. Yet, we know that we must walk their path in order to reach the ‘other side’. Movement equals transition, not only within the physical, but also the metaphysical. The abstract enmeshed within the tangible. I am moving through and within different spheres. By crossing the threshold of the underpass am I heading into the InterZone? Upon exiting will I be the same person? Would I have undergone a rite of passage, however small?
